window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Elegantly styled, Camus' profoundly disturbing novel of a Parisian lawyer's confessions is a searing study of modern amorality.&nbsp;</p> <p>Born in Algeria in 1913, Albert Camus published <i>The Stranger</i> - now one of the most widely read novels of this century - in 1942. Celebrated in intellectual circles, Camus was awarded the Nobel Prize for Literature in 1957.</p>"; 
